<br>
On the video card issues I have an old riva tnt2 card which is not supposed to be supported but due to the fact that I always check out my drivers and see which ones are good you can find out that the newest detonator drivers really cut into the riva tnt2s performance to help out the newer video cards they support.  So all the people with the older cards need to get the older drivers which work perfectly with DirectX 8.1.<br>
<br>
Most of the blame does not need to be put on VI/Sony but rather on the prebuilt computer manufacturers that have for years been selling people crap machines under the guise that the processor is fast.  They get the cheapest crap they can get and buy it in bulk and sell it whether it has issues or not which can lead to some very bad machines that are supposedly top of the line.<br>
<br>
Example:  Last year my fiancee's parents wanted a new computer.  We offered to build them one but since my cousin does not accept credit cards, and they only wanted one without the money to buy one, they were forced to buy a Compaq.  I had spent a few dollars 3 years prior to this to get  my cousins old motherboard and cpu that he was upgrading from.  This is a simple asus board with 266 celeron on it.  I overclocked it to 412 and it runs Luclin fine.  Her computer is a nice compaq 800 that cannot run Luclin and has problems with normal EQ.  Someone want to explain why no one is jumping on Compaq, PB, Dell, and Gateway among others?  <br>
<br>
A lot of this crap is there fault although I do agree that VI should have kept in mind that not everyone gets a good machine some people are forced to buy crap. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=castinareleas>CastinarEleas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/10/01 2:14:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hope the SoL Problems Clear Soon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> why no one is jumping on Compaq, PB, Dell, and Gateway among others? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
